{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/post/2020-03-18-display-image-caption-in-gatsby","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"e794247a-bb80-5eb1-b2ef-0d1aab3cff60","frontmatter":{"title":"Display Image's Caption in Gatsby","hero":{"id":"0769e8b5-007b-5a26-af2d-56abe015fc1d","childImageSharp":{"id":"d5f51d69-248d-596d-b126-e7782d293c08","fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7391304347826086,"src":"/static/65de3fd2547e45ffe3f9d2b91c6598bc/14b42/coding.jpg","srcSet":"/static/65de3fd2547e45ffe3f9d2b91c6598bc/f836f/coding.jpg 200w,\n/static/65de3fd2547e45ffe3f9d2b91c6598bc/2244e/coding.jpg 400w,\n/static/65de3fd2547e45ffe3f9d2b91c6598bc/14b42/coding.jpg 800w,\n/static/65de3fd2547e45ffe3f9d2b91c6598bc/8e2a4/coding.jpg 1140w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}},"date":"2020-03-21","path":"post/2020-03-18-display-image-caption-in-gatsby","tags":["learning-to-code","gatsby","gatsby-remark-images"]},"html":"<p>The caption of the image is very useful in articles. In Markdown syntax there's no place to add a caption to image:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"md\"><pre class=\"language-md\"><code class=\"language-md\"><span class=\"token url\">![<span class=\"token content\">This is alt</span>](here-is-the-url-of-pic <span class=\"token string\">\"Here is the title\"</span>)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Then I found the this article: <a href=\"https://medium.com/@sgpropguide/customising-image-display-in-gatsby-3b027d783dce\">Customising image display in gatsby</a>. It turned out the plugin <code>gatsby-remark-images</code> can do the caption thing for us. We need to set the option <code>showCaptions</code> to \"true\" which in the options of <code>gatsby-remark-images</code> in <code>config.js</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">plugins<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    resolve<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">gatsby-remark-images</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    options<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      maxWidth<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">800</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      showCaptions<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>And the \"title\" in the markdown syntax will automatically show as a caption. We can use the <code>.gatsby-resp-image-figcaption</code> to modify its styles.</p>"},"site":{"id":"Site","siteMetadata":{"title":"CY Is Here"}}},"pageContext":{"pathName":"post/2020-03-18-display-image-caption-in-gatsby","prev":null,"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"post/2020-03-17-gatsby-image","tags":["learning-to-code","gatsby-image","gatsby","100DaysOfGatsby"],"title":"Auto-Optimize Images On MY Gatsby Site"}}}}}